title: President Trump Announces a new Head of Delegation to the Republic of Chile to Attend the Inauguration of His Excellency Sebastián Piñera – The White House
content:
Statements & Releases			

		Foreign Policy	

Issued on:
March 10, 2018
President Donald J. Trump announced the designation of a new Head of Delegation to the Republic of Chile to attend the Inauguration of His Excellency Sebastián Piñera on March 11, 2018, in Valparaiso, Chile.The Honorable Alex M. Azar II, Secretary of Health and Human Services, will lead the delegation.Members of the Presidential Delegation:The Honorable Carol Z. Perez, United States Ambassador to the Republic of Chile
